<br>
<br>
Saffryn and Wardrym have spent several days freeing slaves together in Crushbone, and Saffryn has grudgingly begun to accept that Wardrym is true to his word and ideals about the Koada'Dal exploiting the Fier'Dal.  <br>
<br>
Finding her at her aunt and uncles business, Hearthwood Tavern, he sits at the table with her and sees she's eating a plate of Aviak eggs and Basilisk bacon.  Offering a strip of the bacon to him, she says, &quot;Want some?  Good for your teeth ya know, makes them hard as rocks.&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;Nay, but I will have some of the gnomish java,&quot; he replies and signals to one of the Hearthwood helpers tending to tables.<br>
<br>
&quot;And that's a meal better for breakfast, not dinner,&quot; he adds.<br>
<br>
&quot;Ah, well I was havin' a craving.  These are from Butcherblock and it's there that I travel this eve.  Guild is having a meeting.&quot;<br>
<br>
Ward is served his java and watches the girl eat with a gusto.  &quot;Do you do anything half-way?&quot;  <br>
<br>
&quot;Nope.&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;It ever get you in trouble?&quot; he asks.<br>
<br>
&quot;Yep&quot; she replies with a pirate smile as she wipes up the egg yoke with a piece of toast and stuffs it into her mouth.&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;Anything important going on at the meeting?&quot; he asks.<br>
<br>
&quot;Don't know, but if'n I did, I couldn't tell you ya know.  We may have become friends, but I've made a vow to these people.  I'll not speak of guild matters to those not inside.&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;I can respect that.  Catch up with me later on our plans to get into that Tome?&quot; he asks.<br>
<br>
&quot;You betcha&quot; she replies as she stands, lays some coin on the table for the maid waiting the tables.  &quot;Enjoy your java, sir Prince,&quot; she smirks.<br>
<br>
&quot;Enjoy your meeting,&quot; he replies with a secret smile.<br>
<br>
~~~~********~~~~<br>
<br>
Saffryn arrives at the meeting place and awaits the others to arrive, and one by one, they do.  It is decided where the new guild hall will be built.  There is talk of updating the membership roster. Minz awakens late, pantless, and gets lost on the way to the meeting.  Saffryn chuckles to herself, &quot;It's good to see some things are consistant.&quot;<br>
<br>
The floor is opened and there is one single, shocking announcement.  Windam and her husband, Derakarsis are leaving the Order of the Elder Dragons and joining the Violent Harvest.  At first there is shocked silence.  Then all hell breaks loose as Cressida tries to bring order back to the meeting.  Windam insists it's not her husband's idea, he being a Teir'Dal.  She insists it's all her idea.  <br>
<br>
Saffryn begins to mull over in her mind the consequences of this.  Is Windam going seriously, or is she on a secret spy mission?  What of Saffryn's quest for Windam's necklace?<br>
<br>
&quot;Well,&quot; she ponders to herself as the ruckus continues in the meeting, &quot;If Windam is leaving the Order for the enemy's side, then I have no reason to get her the necklace from Xareth….. which means there is no reason to exchange those spell pages that will stop that curse afflicting Xareth in exchange for the necklace.  Without those pages, no cure.  Without the cure,  the curse will continue to turn Xareth from a Teir'Dal into a Koad' Dal,  a 'Pale Lily', she chuckles.  <br>
<br>
&quot;Oh, Xareth,&quot; she says aloud to no one.  &quot;You're screwed.&quot;<br>
